main event: Multiple UFO sightings were reported in Holmen, Wisconsin between April and June 1952, involving bright, elongated, and blue-colored objects performing unusual aerial maneuvers.
interesting points: The sighting on 17 June 1952 involved Mr. and Mrs. Holmen observing an elongated, brightly illuminated, and rapidly moving object for approximately two minutes.
A separate observation on 18 April 1952 described an object maneuvering rapidly and silently, descending, and emitting flashes of light from both ends.
Another report dated 3 May 1952 detailed a strange object traveling at a steady and uniform direction, emitting brilliance, and changing course rapidly, without any accompanying sound.
One observation described an unusual object the size of a basketball, blue in color, and moving at an unusual speed during a rainstorm.
The documents mention weather conditions and air activity in the vicinity that may have contributed to poor visibility and precluded the satisfactory identification of these objects.
sighted object: bright, elongated, and blue-colored objects performing unusual aerial maneuvers
witnesses: civilian witnesses, including Mr. and Mrs. Holmen and Capt. Rupe
